Define desired capabilities or outcomes that new epics may validly serve.

| ID | Desired Capability / Outcome | Source Reference | Epic Authoring Implication |
|---|---|---|---|

Rules:

- Use exact Core terminology.
- Include only capabilities relevant to authoring new epics.
- Do not infer whether any capability currently exists.
- Do not map to any specific proposal.

## Epic Authoring Principles

Define what a first authoritative epic should contain.

| ID | Authoring Principle | Meaning | Required Behavior |
|---|---|---|---|

Include principles for:

- strategic purpose
- desired capability
- projection alignment
- repository grounding
- bounded scope
- explicit non-goals
- assumptions
- dependencies
- constraints
