## Repository Grounding Rules

Define how repository evidence should shape new epic authoring.

| ID | Repository Finding Pattern | Strategic Interpretation | Authoring Behavior |
|---|---|---|---|

Examples of Repository Finding Pattern:

- related capability already exists
- related capability partially exists
- relevant abstraction already exists
- repository suggests better capability boundary
- repository reveals missing foundation
- repository reveals compatibility boundary
- repository reveals architectural commitment
- repository evidence is insufficient

Do not include actual repository facts.

## Abstraction Selection Rules

Define how the downstream prompt should choose the right abstraction for the new epic.

| ID | Abstraction Case | Selection Rule | Success Signal |
|---|---|---|---|

Examples of Abstraction Case:

- proposal is implementation-first
- proposal spans multiple responsibilities
- proposal maps to an existing domain concept
- proposal requires a missing foundation
- proposal duplicates existing responsibility
- proposal should be anchored in platform capability
- proposal should be anchored in user outcome
- proposal should be anchored in semantic boundary

## Scope Derivation Rules

Define how the downstream prompt should derive epic scope.

| ID | Scope Case | Derivation Rule | Guardrail |
|---|---|---|---|

Examples:

- proposal underspecified
- proposal overbroad
- proposal includes unrelated downstream work
- proposal omits required foundation
- proposal risks duplicating existing capability
- proposal needs clear non-goals
- proposal should enable but not implement dependent epics

## Dependency Derivation Rules

Define how dependencies should be identified and represented.

| ID | Dependency Pattern | Derivation Rule | Epic Implication |
|---|---|---|---|

Examples:

- strategic dependency
- architectural dependency
- semantic dependency
- compatibility dependency
- repository dependency
- validation dependency
- unresolved dependency
- dependency that should become required follow-up

